[Michael] You sure?

975
00:50:45.499 --> 00:50:47.918
Yeah. I think I'd remember.

976
00:50:48.794 --> 00:50:50.004
Who are you?

977
00:50:50.713 --> 00:50:52.048
John Branca.

978
00:50:53.507 --> 00:50:54.884
You handle The Beach Boys.

979
00:50:54.967 --> 00:50:56.218
[Branca] Yeah. I do.

980
00:50:56.302 --> 00:50:59.638
Neil Diamond. Bob Dylan.
couple other guys. and now I work here.

981
00:51:00.931 --> 00:51:02.224
I like The Beach Boys.

982
00:51:02.308 --> 00:51:03.350
Me too.

983
00:51:03.434 --> 00:51:04.977
Brian Wilson's a genius.

984
00:51:05.061 --> 00:51:07.021
Some of the best harmonies
in rock and roll.

985
00:51:11.317 --> 00:51:13.319
You know what I'm after. Mr. Branca?

986
00:51:13.402 --> 00:51:14.445
[Branca] Sure.

987
00:51:15.488 --> 00:51:17.281
You want to be
the biggest star in the world.

988
00:51:21.577 --> 00:51:23.245
Can you help make that happen?

989
00:51:24.330 --> 00:51:25.456
Yes.

990
00:51:26.874 --> 00:51:28.167
How?

991
00:51:29.335 --> 00:51:32.588
Because I believe there's no one like you.

992
00:51:33.964 --> 00:51:35.758
And there never will be.

993
00:51:44.475 --> 00:51:45.643
[man 1] Mr. Jackson...

994
00:51:47.603 --> 00:51:50.272
- Mr. Jackson. I apologize--
- He's my guy.

995
00:51:55.069 --> 00:51:56.946
Can you leave us alone for a second?

996
00:51:57.947 --> 00:51:58.864
Please.

997
00:51:59.657 --> 00:52:00.825
[man 1] Of course.

998
00:52:01.408 --> 00:52:02.326
Yes.

999
00:52:08.165 --> 00:52:09.583
[door opens]

1000
00:52:13.879 --> 00:52:14.880
[door closes]

1001
00:52:15.381 --> 00:52:16.966
Okay. Mr. Branca.

1002
00:52:17.049 --> 00:52:20.136
- [clears throat]
- Here's your first job.

1003
00:52:22.221 --> 00:52:23.848
I need you to fire Joseph.

1004
00:52:26.559 --> 00:52:27.560
Your dad?

1005
00:52:28.310 --> 00:52:29.728
You want me to fire your dad?

1006
00:52:31.105 --> 00:52:32.690
And how would you like me to do that?

1007
00:52:34.066 --> 00:52:35.192
Quickly.

1008
00:52:37.570 --> 00:52:39.363
[plucking notes guitar]

1009
00:52:40.573 --> 00:52:43.200
[machine beeps. whirring]

1010
00:52:44.451 --> 00:52:46.453
[''Wanna Be Startin' Somethin'''
instrumental playing]

1011
00:53:00.593 --> 00:53:03.053
[music stops]

1012
00:53:03.137 --> 00:53:04.889
- Yes.
- I think it goes...

1013
00:53:04.972 --> 00:53:06.140
Button it up like this.

1014
00:53:06.223 --> 00:53:07.266
- Oh. right.
- Yeah.

1015
00:53:07.349 --> 00:53:09.727
La Toya. get the hell on out of here.

1016
00:53:11.228 --> 00:53:13.522
Kate. look at this.

1017
00:53:13.606 --> 00:53:14.732
Will you look at this?

1018
00:53:14.815 --> 00:53:17.359
The boy fired me with a piece of paper.

1019
00:53:18.235 --> 00:53:20.070
A piece of--
Couldn't even be man to man. huh?

1020
00:53:20.154 --> 00:53:21.739
Look me in the eye and do it.

1021
00:53:22.281 --> 00:53:24.366
That boy's gonna feel my belt
when he get in here!

1022
00:53:26.076 --> 00:53:27.161
No. he's not.

1023
00:53:28.120 --> 00:53:29.163
Yes. the hell he is.

1024
00:53:29.246 --> 00:53:30.414
No. he's not.

1025
00:53:30.998 --> 00:53:32.541
What are you gonna do. beat him?

1026
00:53:33.125 --> 00:53:34.501
You're gonna whoop him?

1027
00:53:35.377 --> 00:53:36.545
He's grown.

1028
00:53:36.629 --> 00:53:37.880
What'd you say to me?

1029
00:53:41.091 --> 00:53:43.093
I said you can't do it no more.

1030
00:53:44.595 --> 00:53:45.971
You can't whoop nobody.

1031
00:53:47.640 --> 00:53:49.266
You can't beat nobody.

1032
00:53:51.644 --> 00:53:53.854
And if you don't like it. you can leave.

1033
00:53:59.276 --> 00:54:00.903
And the next time you see your son.

1034
00:54:00.986 --> 00:54:02.821
you ought to thank him.

1035
00:54:02.905 --> 00:54:05.282
Everything we have is because of him

1036
00:54:05.366 --> 00:54:06.700
and don't you ever forget that.

1037
00:54:06.784 --> 00:54:08.118
Everybody seems to forget

1038
00:54:08.869 --> 00:54:10.871
that I'm the one that got us out of Gary.

1039
00:54:12.790 --> 00:54:15.000
And everything I've done

1040
00:54:15.793 --> 00:54:17.461
is for this family.

1041
00:54:18.045 --> 00:54:20.464
You go on ahead and keep thinking that.

1042
00:54:23.509 --> 00:54:25.302
[distant rustling]

1043
00:54:27.429 --> 00:54:28.639
[''Enjoy Yourself" by The Jacksons playing]

1044
00:54:28.722 --> 00:54:29.556
[giraffe grunts]

1045
00:54:32.893 --> 00:54:34.895
♪ <i>Enjoy yourself. enjoy yourself♪</i>

1046
00:54:34.979 --> 00:54:36.981
♪ <i>Enjoy yourself with me</i> ♪

1047
00:54:37.064 --> 00:54:39.108
♪ <i>Enjoy yourself. enjoy yourself♪</i>

1048
00:54:39.191 --> 00:54:41.318
♪ <i>Enjoy yourself with me</i> ♪

1049
00:54:41.402 --> 00:54:43.821
♪ <i>You better enjoy yourself...</i> ♪

1050
00:54:46.115 --> 00:54:47.032
[loud pop]

1051
00:54:48.033 --> 00:54:50.369
- [chuckling]
- [laughs]

1052
00:54:51.787 --> 00:54:52.997
[Michael] <i>You didn't go down this side.</i>

1053
00:54:53.080 --> 00:54:54.707
- Where? Left?
- Left.

1054
00:54:54.790 --> 00:54:57.126
- Going left. All right.
- [toy train whistle blows]

1055
00:54:59.420 --> 00:55:00.713
A little choo-choo train.

1056
00:55:00.796 --> 00:55:02.423
- [Michael] I love it.
- [chuckles]

1057
00:55:04.341 --> 00:55:05.259
Hi.

1058
00:55:06.218 --> 00:55:07.720
[indistinct chatter]

1059
00:55:07.803 --> 00:55:09.179
So. I'm really excited.

1060
00:55:09.263 --> 00:55:10.472
- This looks really cool.
- [Bill] Look. it's you.

1061
00:55:10.556 --> 00:55:11.557
[Michael] That's you. [chuckles]

1062
00:55:11.640 --> 00:55:13.976
- [boy] I can't wait to start playing it.
- [woman] That's Michael Jackson.

1063
00:55:14.059 --> 00:55:15.352
- What?
- It's Michael Jackson.

1064
00:55:15.436 --> 00:55:16.353
What?

1065
00:55:17.730 --> 00:55:19.231
Please excuse him. [chuckles]

1066
00:55:19.315 --> 00:55:22.401
[sputtering] Are you actually. really...

1067
00:55:22.484 --> 00:55:23.902
Yeah. I'm Michael. yeah.

1068
00:55:23.986 --> 00:55:25.612
- Wow.
- Mom. it's...

1069
00:55:25.696 --> 00:55:26.864
- I wonder...
- Oh. my God.

1070
00:55:26.947 --> 00:55:30.784
I'd love an autograph.
For my son. I mean. [chuckles]

1071
00:55:31.368 --> 00:55:33.162
Of course. yeah. Um...

1072
00:55:33.245 --> 00:55:34.955
He's a huge fan.

1073
00:55:35.914 --> 00:55:39.001
Here. How about I sign this?
What's your name?

1074
00:55:39.084 --> 00:55:40.919
Uh. you can just make it out to...

1075
00:55:41.003 --> 00:55:42.838
- Pauline.
- Mom?

1076
00:55:43.422 --> 00:55:45.090
- Pauline. [chuckles]
- [boy] Mom?

1077
00:55:45.174 --> 00:55:47.051
Mom. my name's Max. not Pauline.

1078
00:55:47.134 --> 00:55:48.552
- [shushing]
- I'm not Pauline.

1079
00:55:48.635 --> 00:55:50.262
Is that the new Atari game?

1080
00:55:51.221 --> 00:55:52.681
- I love that.
- You've played it?

1081
00:55:52.765 --> 00:55:54.641
Oh. yeah. all the time.

1082
00:55:55.351 --> 00:55:57.978
Just be sure to keep toggling left
when you fire.

1083
00:55:58.062 --> 00:55:59.188
That's how you power up.

1084
00:55:59.271 --> 00:56:01.273
Cool. Thank you.

1085
00:56:01.357 --> 00:56:02.441
[Michael] Of course.

1086
00:56:03.275 --> 00:56:04.485
Hi.

1087
00:56:05.069 --> 00:56:06.862
- Would you like an autograph?
- Yes. please.

1088
00:56:06.945 --> 00:56:08.864
- What's your name?
- Monica.

1089
00:56:08.947 --> 00:56:10.824
Monica. That's a pretty name.

1090
00:56:10.908 --> 00:56:13.118
- [man] What do you say. baby?
- [Monica] Thank you.

1091
00:56:13.202 --> 00:56:14.620
[woman] We're huge fans. Michael.

1092
00:56:14.703 --> 00:56:16.080
[Michael] Thank you so much.

1093
00:56:19.750 --> 00:56:22.336
- Thanks.
- Hey. everybody. Too cute.

1094
00:56:22.419 --> 00:56:24.421
- [rattling]
- [indistinct chatter]

1095
00:56:25.381 --> 00:56:27.508
- [vehicle approaching]
- [chattering]

1096
00:56:29.718 --> 00:56:30.552
[chains clink]

1097
00:56:32.304 --> 00:56:33.555
- [Tito] Here. here. I got it.
- [Marlon] Oh...

1098
00:56:34.181 --> 00:56:36.266
- Hey!
- [Jermaine] Hey. Mikey! What's up. Mikey?

1099
00:56:36.350 --> 00:56:37.434
- All right. jokers.
- What's up. Bill?

1100
00:56:37.518 --> 00:56:38.394
[Tito] What's up. Bill?

1101
00:56:39.645 --> 00:56:41.063
- [Jermaine] Ahh!
- [Jackie] Too short.

1102
00:56:41.146 --> 00:56:44.024
[brothers chattering]

1103
00:56:44.108 --> 00:56:45.192
[Michael] Guys. look!

1104
00:56:45.275 --> 00:56:46.735
I got Twister.

1105
00:56:46.819 --> 00:56:48.654
- Twister?
- You want to play tonight?

1106
00:56:48.737 --> 00:56:49.738
- Fucking Twister?
- Really?

1107
00:56:49.822 --> 00:56:51.031
What we gonna do with Twister. man?

1108
00:56:51.115 --> 00:56:52.324
Come on. It'll be like the old days.

1109
00:56:52.991 --> 00:56:55.869
Would love to. Mike. but I got to be home
with the family. I can't be playing games.

1110
00:56:55.953 --> 00:56:57.871
[Marlon] And the rest of us
are going out tonight.

1111
00:56:57.955 --> 00:56:59.540
[Tito] Yeah. Marlon's got a hot date.

1112
00:56:59.623 --> 00:57:00.707
- [Marlon] Yeah.
- [brothers laugh]

1113
00:57:00.791 --> 00:57:03.085
Marlon. what time are you gonna be home?
We could play then.

1114
00:57:03.168 --> 00:57:05.170
Hey. Marlon's gonna be playing
his own game of Twister.

1115
00:57:05.254 --> 00:57:06.630
- [brothers exclaim]
- [Marlon] Shut up. Jackie.

1116
00:57:06.713 --> 00:57:08.507
- I'm always lucky.
- [brothers laugh]

1117
00:57:08.590 --> 00:57:09.591
[Jackie] Yeah. right.

1118
00:57:10.426 --> 00:57:12.428
- You guys are no fun anymore.
- [Jermaine] Come on. Mike.

1119
00:57:12.511 --> 00:57:13.637
Don't be like that.

1120
00:57:13.720 --> 00:57:16.140
[''Blame it On The Boogie''
By The Jacksons playing]

1121
00:57:17.141 --> 00:57:18.559
Hey. that's cheating.

1122
00:57:18.642 --> 00:57:21.854
You got red. not green. [laughing]

1123
00:57:25.774 --> 00:57:27.067
It's okay.

1124
00:57:27.151 --> 00:57:28.569
Don't worry about it.

1125
00:57:28.652 --> 00:57:30.654
It takes a long time to learn

1126
00:57:30.737 --> 00:57:33.532
and I'm a professional dancer. [chuckles]

1127
00:57:34.825 --> 00:57:35.909
You want some ice cream?

1128
00:57:37.202 --> 00:57:38.912
Okay. but then I've got to go to work.

1129
00:57:39.663 --> 00:57:40.873
Don't break anything.

1130
00:57:41.582 --> 00:57:42.666
I'll be back.

1131
00:57:43.792 --> 00:57:46.253
♪ <i>Don't you blame it on the sunshine</i> ♪

1132
00:57:46.336 --> 00:57:48.255
♪ <i>Don't blame it on the moonlight</i> ♪

1133
00:57:48.338 --> 00:57:50.507
♪ <i>Don't blame it on the good times</i> ♪

1134
00:57:50.591 --> 00:57:52.468
♪ <i>Blame it on the boogie</i> ♪

1135
00:57:52.551 --> 00:57:53.886
[Bubbles grunting]

1136
00:57:53.969 --> 00:57:56.138
[Michael humming]

1137
00:58:01.643 --> 00:58:03.687
- [music stops]
- [Michael exhales softly]

1138
00:58:08.358 --> 00:58:10.235
I was thinkin' about framing this.

1139
00:58:16.575 --> 00:58:17.659
Read it.

1140
00:58:19.995 --> 00:58:21.371
Go on. Read it.

1141
00:58:26.919 --> 00:58:28.545
Firing your own father.

1142
00:58:29.671 --> 00:58:31.340
What kind of son does that?

1143
00:58:37.346 --> 00:58:39.348
[sighs] Michael...

1144
00:58:42.267 --> 00:58:44.269
You got a lot to learn about family.

1145
00:58:54.238 --> 00:58:55.739
[door closes]

1146
00:58:55.822 --> 00:58:57.407
[''The Love You Save'' by Jackson 5 playing]

1147
00:58:57.491 --> 00:59:00.077
♪ <i>Stop! Na na na!
You'd better save it</i> ♪

1148
00:59:00.160 --> 00:59:03.997
♪ <i>Stop. stop. stop. you'd better save it</i> ♪

1149
00:59:04.081 --> 00:59:05.499
♪ <i>Whoo</i> ♪

1150
00:59:08.377 --> 00:59:10.337
- Hi. Welcome back. Michael.
- Hi.

1151
00:59:10.921 --> 00:59:12.089
[Michael] Beautiful name.

1152
00:59:12.172 --> 00:59:13.090
[photographer] Look up for us.

1153
00:59:13.173 --> 00:59:15.384
♪ <i>When we played tag in grade school</i> ♪

1154
00:59:16.343 --> 00:59:17.678
[Michael] This is for you.

1155
00:59:19.638 --> 00:59:21.640
♪ <i>You crossed your heart you'd quit</i> ♪

1156
00:59:21.723 --> 00:59:23.892
♪ <i>When we grew up. you traded</i> ♪

1157
00:59:23.976 --> 00:59:25.852
♪ <i>Your promise for my ring</i> ♪

1158
00:59:25.936 --> 00:59:26.937
[photographer 2] Michael over here.

1159
00:59:27.813 --> 00:59:29.815
♪ <i>You're doing the same old thing...</i> ♪

1160
00:59:29.898 --> 00:59:32.985
<i>You want to say that again.
transistor face?</i>

1161
00:59:33.819 --> 00:59:35.445
You watch TV?

1162
00:59:35.529 --> 00:59:38.156
Yeah. Sometimes.

1163
00:59:38.824 --> 00:59:40.450
You watch TV?

1164
00:59:40.534 --> 00:59:42.744
- Yeah.
- [TV continues indistinctly]

1165
00:59:42.828 --> 00:59:44.037
Cartoons.

1166
00:59:44.913 --> 00:59:46.540
<i>Three Stooges</i> a lot.

1167
00:59:48.000 --> 00:59:49.251
Charlie Chaplin.

1168
00:59:50.627 --> 00:59:51.837
You know who he is?

1169
00:59:52.796 --> 00:59:54.715
- Duh.
- No. you don't.

1170
00:59:55.549 --> 00:59:56.842
You're such a doo-doo head.

1171
00:59:58.093 --> 01:00:00.220
He's wonderful. really.

1172
01:00:00.304 --> 01:00:03.181
He's an actor. he's a movie director...

1173
01:00:04.057 --> 01:00:05.684
and he writes songs.

1174
01:00:07.561 --> 01:00:09.771
I have a dog.

1175
01:00:09.855 --> 01:00:11.189
It's a dachshund.

1176
01:00:11.773 --> 01:00:14.401
Mm. What's his name?

1177
01:00:14.484 --> 01:00:15.569
Rudy.

1178
01:00:16.320 --> 01:00:17.404
He's getting fat.

1179
01:00:17.487 --> 01:00:19.906
My mom says I feed him too much.

1180
01:00:19.990 --> 01:00:22.200
[chuckling] I love Rudy.

1181
01:00:22.284 --> 01:00:24.119
Do you have any pets?

1182
01:00:24.995 --> 01:00:27.956
Uh... A snake

1183
01:00:28.040 --> 01:00:29.458
and a giraffe.

1184
01:00:29.541 --> 01:00:30.751
No way.

1185
01:00:30.834 --> 01:00:32.044
And a llama.

1186
01:00:33.086 --> 01:00:35.047
[woman indistinct over P.A.]

1187
01:00:35.130 --> 01:00:37.841
[muffled] And three parrots. two spiders.

1188
01:00:37.924 --> 01:00:40.260
and a whole lot of dogs.

1189
01:00:40.344 --> 01:00:42.346
[indistinct chattering]

1190
01:00:43.680 --> 01:00:46.308
[Michael] It's got to be
the greatest-selling album of all time.

1191
01:00:47.267 --> 01:00:49.603
And not just by a Black artist

1192
01:00:49.686 --> 01:00:52.564
but by any race. any color. okay?

1193
01:00:52.648 --> 01:00:55.734
Then I want the largest
concert tour there ever was.

1194
01:00:55.817 --> 01:00:57.319
Just stadiums only.

1195
01:00:57.402 --> 01:00:58.654
Just thousands and thousands of people

1196
01:00:58.737 --> 01:01:01.865
just rushing into the stadiums
and just all over the world.

1197
01:01:02.449 --> 01:01:05.243
I also want to make short films
featuring my music.

1198
01:01:05.327 --> 01:01:06.411
That's ambitious.

1199
01:01:06.495 --> 01:01:07.746
I can see it.

1200
01:01:07.829 --> 01:01:09.956
You see it. You can do it.

1201
01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:11.875
And l-I see it so clearly.

1202
01:01:12.918 --> 01:01:16.421
Well. Walter Yetnikoff called.
CBS wants to do a press release.

1203
01:01:16.505 --> 01:01:20.759
No. No press. no interviews. no nothing.

1204
01:01:21.635 --> 01:01:23.053
Well. he's not gonna like that.

1205
01:01:24.137 --> 01:01:25.889
You got to handle that. Branca.

1206
01:01:26.682 --> 01:01:27.766
You see...

1207
01:01:28.809 --> 01:01:30.435
I want to be mysterious.

1208
01:01:31.103 --> 01:01:32.187
Like-- Like Garbo.

1209
01:01:33.063 --> 01:01:34.272
You know. but. uh...

1210
01:01:34.356 --> 01:01:36.858
I mean. if Halley's Comet came every year.

1211
01:01:36.942 --> 01:01:40.195
just year after year.
would you look at it?

1212
01:01:41.738 --> 01:01:43.156
You're gonna need publicity.

1213
01:01:43.740 --> 01:01:46.827
What I'm gonna need is
a good record that sells.

1214
01:01:46.910 --> 01:01:49.204
- Nothing else matters.
- Fair enough.

1215
01:01:49.287 --> 01:01:52.207
Then I suggest you start laying down
some killer demos.

1216
01:01:53.125 --> 01:01:55.544
- Can you do that?
- [chuckles]

1217
01:01:55.627 --> 01:01:57.462
Of course. I can do that.

1218
01:01:58.338 --> 01:01:59.673
[''Think Happy'' by The Jacksons playing]

1219
01:01:59.756 --> 01:02:01.341
[scatting indistinctly]

1220
01:02:01.425 --> 01:02:03.927
[chuckles]
What are you doing. Mike?

1221
01:02:04.010 --> 01:02:05.095
I'm channeling.

1222
01:02:06.596 --> 01:02:09.099
I'm letting the Creator
give me a song right now.

