01:26:43.155 --> 01:26:44.990
- Night. Mother.
- Good night.

1690
01:26:45.073 --> 01:26:46.909
[music continues on TV]

1691
01:26:49.369 --> 01:26:50.787
[chuckles]

1692
01:26:50.871 --> 01:26:52.873
[humming softly]

1693
01:26:55.667 --> 01:26:56.752
[switch clicks]

1694
01:26:57.628 --> 01:26:59.463
[continues humming]

1695
01:27:00.380 --> 01:27:02.007
[scatting softly]

1696
01:27:15.687 --> 01:27:16.897
[stops scatting. gasps]

1697
01:27:21.443 --> 01:27:22.653
Why are you here?

1698
01:27:23.779 --> 01:27:25.781
What? Can't a father visit his son?

1699
01:27:28.283 --> 01:27:30.702
Biggest-selling record of all time

1700
01:27:31.370 --> 01:27:33.372
from a poor kid from Gary.

1701
01:27:34.081 --> 01:27:35.082
Who would have thought?

1702
01:27:36.124 --> 01:27:38.835
Me. I thought.

1703
01:27:38.919 --> 01:27:40.545
[chuckles]

1704
01:27:44.258 --> 01:27:45.342
Come here.

1705
01:27:46.802 --> 01:27:48.637
Joseph. I know you want something.

1706
01:27:53.558 --> 01:27:54.768
Michael...

1707
01:27:56.770 --> 01:27:58.981
I'm gonna need you to tour
with your brothers.

1708
01:28:00.565 --> 01:28:03.068
Now. I let you do that album by yourself.

1709
01:28:04.236 --> 01:28:05.988
I'm gonna need you to do this for me.

1710
01:28:07.864 --> 01:28:08.949
For your family.

1711
01:28:10.534 --> 01:28:12.703
I'm not a child anymore. Joseph.

1712
01:28:12.786 --> 01:28:13.704
[sighs]

1713
01:28:13.787 --> 01:28:15.497
- And you're not my manager.
- Here we go.

1714
01:28:15.580 --> 01:28:17.708
I have to start living my own life.

1715
01:28:19.710 --> 01:28:20.919
On my own.

1716
01:28:21.962 --> 01:28:23.588
Just like everyone else.

1717
01:28:23.672 --> 01:28:25.424
You ain't like everyone else.

1718
01:28:28.427 --> 01:28:31.305
So. you're trying to tell me
you want to be treated like an adult?

1719
01:28:32.472 --> 01:28:33.890
All right.

1720
01:28:33.974 --> 01:28:37.644
You want to see what the world is like

1721
01:28:38.854 --> 01:28:40.814
without a family that protects you.

1722
01:28:42.232 --> 01:28:44.651
- [door creaks]
- Without a family that...

1723
01:28:45.652 --> 01:28:46.737
understands you.

1724
01:28:47.821 --> 01:28:51.241
Nobody else will understand you
outside this place.

1725
01:28:51.325 --> 01:28:54.202
There you'll be with
all the money in the world.

1726
01:28:54.286 --> 01:28:56.204
surrounded by people who'll say ''yes''

1727
01:28:57.080 --> 01:28:59.499
to everything. [chuckles]

1728
01:29:00.792 --> 01:29:02.002
Is that what you want?

1729
01:29:06.757 --> 01:29:08.091
What kind of sense that make?

1730
01:29:16.516 --> 01:29:17.517
I'm gonna...

1731
01:29:18.226 --> 01:29:19.519
call Don King

1732
01:29:20.228 --> 01:29:22.064
and tell him you're doing a tour.

1733
01:29:24.691 --> 01:29:26.651
I know you don't want to let
your family down.

1734
01:29:31.073 --> 01:29:34.076
[Michael breathing deeply]

1735
01:29:45.837 --> 01:29:47.255
[sighs]

1736
01:29:47.339 --> 01:29:49.383
[''Billie Jean'' by Michael Jackson playing]

1737
01:29:49.466 --> 01:29:50.926
[crowd cheering loudly]

1738
01:29:57.974 --> 01:30:00.477
♪ <i>You're a whole new generation</i> ♪

1739
01:30:00.560 --> 01:30:02.396
♪ <i>You're Iovin' what you do</i> ♪

1740
01:30:02.479 --> 01:30:04.481
♪ <i>Put a Pepsi in the motion</i> ♪

1741
01:30:04.564 --> 01:30:06.817
♪ <i>That choice is up to you. hey-ey</i> ♪

1742
01:30:06.900 --> 01:30:08.819
[man] Cut! Cut! Cut! Cut!

1743
01:30:08.902 --> 01:30:11.029
- [music stops]
- [cheering fades]

1744
01:30:11.780 --> 01:30:14.116
All right. here's what I need.
I'm thinking...

1745
01:30:15.742 --> 01:30:18.370
I move the camera in while you're up here.

1746
01:30:18.453 --> 01:30:21.289
I need to get a close up
of you at the top.

1747
01:30:21.373 --> 01:30:23.542
so just feel the camera as you come down.

1748
01:30:23.625 --> 01:30:25.293
- Okay.
- Okay. great. All right.

1749
01:30:25.377 --> 01:30:27.629
Okay. everybody. [grunts]

1750
01:30:27.712 --> 01:30:31.425
Here we go. What is this?
What do we got? Take six?

1751
01:30:31.508 --> 01:30:32.884
Lucky six. Lucky six.

1752
01:30:32.968 --> 01:30:34.594
Here we go. Energy. everybody!

1753
01:30:34.678 --> 01:30:37.180
You love The Jacksons.
You love The Jacksons.

1754
01:30:37.264 --> 01:30:39.099
You love Pepsi. Let's go!

1755
01:30:40.308 --> 01:30:41.893
- [woman] A marker!
- [marker snaps]

1756
01:30:41.977 --> 01:30:44.020
- [man 2] B mark!
- [marker snaps]

1757
01:30:44.104 --> 01:30:45.188
- [man 3] C mark.
- [audience cheering]

1758
01:30:45.272 --> 01:30:46.898
[man 1] And playback.

1759
01:30:48.650 --> 01:30:49.985
[''Billie Jean'' playing]

1760
01:30:53.363 --> 01:30:54.823
[fireworks explode]

1761
01:31:04.583 --> 01:31:06.042
- [music fades]
- [sizzling]

1762
01:31:06.126 --> 01:31:07.419
[muffled cheering]

1763
01:31:09.838 --> 01:31:12.007
[whimpering]

1764
01:31:14.092 --> 01:31:14.968
[screaming]

1765
01:31:15.051 --> 01:31:16.178
Cut it.

1766
01:31:16.261 --> 01:31:18.180
[people clamoring]

1767
01:31:20.307 --> 01:31:21.391
[Bill] Michael!

1768
01:31:21.475 --> 01:31:22.976
- [all clamoring]
- [Michael groaning]

1769
01:31:23.059 --> 01:31:24.227
What happened?

1770
01:31:25.395 --> 01:31:27.063
- Mike. are you okay?
- [Bill] Back up!

1771
01:31:27.147 --> 01:31:29.524
- Bill. get him out of here!
- Here. Michael!

1772
01:31:30.358 --> 01:31:31.318
Over here. Joker. Come here.

1773
01:31:31.401 --> 01:31:33.320
Hey. you're gonna be okay. okay?
You're gonna be okay.

1774
01:31:33.403 --> 01:31:34.779
[Bill] Come on. Mike. Clear a path!

1775
01:31:34.863 --> 01:31:37.532
[people screaming and clamoring]

1776
01:31:38.241 --> 01:31:40.285
[Bill] Out of my way!
Michael. I'm coming!

1777
01:31:41.369 --> 01:31:43.663
Get back! Get out of my way! Clear a path!

1778
01:31:43.747 --> 01:31:45.749
Get back! Get back!

1779
01:31:46.666 --> 01:31:49.878
Clear a path! Move! Move. please!

1780
01:31:49.961 --> 01:31:51.254
Michael!

1781
01:31:51.338 --> 01:31:52.589
- [muffled wailing]
- [tense music playing]

1782
01:31:52.672 --> 01:31:53.882
[Bill] Excuse me!

1783
01:31:55.425 --> 01:31:57.260
[crying]

1784
01:32:06.853 --> 01:32:08.813
[phone ringing]

1785
01:32:08.897 --> 01:32:10.106
[Joseph exhales]

1786
01:32:24.371 --> 01:32:26.122
Kate. Kate. come on.

1787
01:32:28.458 --> 01:32:30.377
- Hey. I need to talk to you.
- Sir.

1788
01:32:30.460 --> 01:32:32.087
I'm his father. Joseph Jackson.

1789
01:32:32.170 --> 01:32:33.672
This is his mother. Katherine.

1790
01:32:33.755 --> 01:32:35.549
- Hi. It's good to meet you.
- Very nice to meet you.

1791
01:32:35.632 --> 01:32:36.883
Thank you.

1792
01:32:36.967 --> 01:32:39.469
Well. your son is in stable condition.

1793
01:32:39.553 --> 01:32:40.929
- All right.
- [doctor] All right?

1794
01:32:41.012 --> 01:32:43.306
And. uh. we're trying to bring
his heart rate down.

1795
01:32:43.390 --> 01:32:44.766
but he's in a lot of pain.

1796
01:32:46.184 --> 01:32:47.602
Okay. When will he recover?

1797
01:32:47.686 --> 01:32:48.812
It's too soon to tell.

1798
01:32:49.729 --> 01:32:51.690
It's gonna be a long road. all right?

1799
01:32:51.773 --> 01:32:54.776
He has third-degree burns
and substantial nerve damage.

1800
01:32:56.903 --> 01:32:57.904
[Joseph] Okay.

1801
01:32:58.697 --> 01:33:01.783
Do you think he'll ever be able
to perform again?

1802
01:33:01.866 --> 01:33:02.784
Ever?

1803
01:33:03.368 --> 01:33:04.744
[Katherine] Joseph.

1804
01:33:08.206 --> 01:33:11.418
Mr. Jackson. your son almost died.

1805
01:33:11.501 --> 01:33:12.836
I know that.

1806
01:33:12.919 --> 01:33:14.838
Well. if that fire had caught his clothes.

1807
01:33:14.921 --> 01:33:17.799
or burned over to his face
and eyes. he wouldn't be here.

1808
01:33:17.882 --> 01:33:19.092
I know my boy.

1809
01:33:19.926 --> 01:33:23.763
And the only thing that's gonna heal him
is by getting back on that stage.

1810
01:33:24.806 --> 01:33:26.433
That's where he lives.

1811
01:33:26.516 --> 01:33:28.101
[doctor] I understand that. sir.

1812
01:33:28.184 --> 01:33:29.561
- But it's gonna be a while.
- Do you? All right.

1813
01:33:29.644 --> 01:33:31.646
[doctor] Yes. I do. But. Mr. Jackson...

1814
01:33:32.522 --> 01:33:35.025
he's gonna need your support to get there.

1815
01:33:35.108 --> 01:33:36.526
I'm sorry.

1816
01:33:38.820 --> 01:33:39.821
[exhales]

1817
01:33:41.698 --> 01:33:43.074
[crowd shouting indistinctly
in the distance]

1818
01:33:43.158 --> 01:33:44.951
[doctor] It's unlikely
that will grow back.

1819
01:33:45.952 --> 01:33:49.039
You'll need surgery
to laser the scar tissue

1820
01:33:49.122 --> 01:33:51.750
and stretch part of the scalp
over the burn.

1821
01:33:52.834 --> 01:33:56.087
All right? We'll insert an implant
to protect the scalp.

1822
01:33:56.171 --> 01:33:58.006
Will I have to wear a wig?

1823
01:33:58.089 --> 01:33:59.591
Well. right there on top.

1824
01:34:02.010 --> 01:34:04.429
What kind of wig? Like. a full wig?

1825
01:34:04.512 --> 01:34:05.764
Hard to say.

1826
01:34:05.847 --> 01:34:08.099
There are prosthetic hair weaves
we can try.

1827
01:34:08.183 --> 01:34:11.353
but we won't know until we see
how the surgery goes next week.

1828
01:34:12.187 --> 01:34:14.606
[crowd chanting in distance]
Michael! Michael! Michael!

1829
01:34:14.689 --> 01:34:17.859
[woman indistinct over P.A.]

1830
01:34:19.527 --> 01:34:20.737
You'll. um...

1831
01:34:21.696 --> 01:34:23.865
You'll have to stay
on the Demerol for a while.

1832
01:34:23.948 --> 01:34:25.700
I don't want to take medication.

1833
01:34:26.409 --> 01:34:29.287
I have to be honest. Mr. Jackson.
you're gonna need them.

1834
01:34:30.121 --> 01:34:32.374
We have to replace
the implant periodically.

1835
01:34:32.457 --> 01:34:34.501
The nerves are exposed up there.

1836
01:34:34.584 --> 01:34:36.294
You'll be in a lot of pain.

1837
01:34:39.172 --> 01:34:41.800
I'll let you rest. but I'll be back later.

1838
01:34:45.220 --> 01:34:47.806
[chanting continues]
Michael! Michael! Michael!

1839
01:34:47.889 --> 01:34:50.141
[woman shouting] We'll stay here
'till you're better. Michael.

1840
01:34:50.225 --> 01:34:51.601
[reporter] You see the number of people

1841
01:34:51.685 --> 01:34:53.895
who have already gathered
outside the hospital.

1842
01:34:53.978 --> 01:34:55.605
If that isn't a testament

1843
01:34:55.689 --> 01:34:58.274
to the star power of Michael Jackson.
I don't know what is.

1844
01:34:58.358 --> 01:35:00.652
The fans say they won't go back
until Michael Jackson's all right.

1845
01:35:01.486 --> 01:35:03.488
[TV playing indistinctly]

1846
01:35:03.571 --> 01:35:04.989
All right.

1847
01:35:05.073 --> 01:35:06.491
All right. Joker.

1848
01:35:07.117 --> 01:35:08.535
Got all your favorites.

1849
01:35:08.618 --> 01:35:10.704
Golden Temple. they send their love.

1850
01:35:10.787 --> 01:35:12.622
- Got some Mexican.
- Golden Temple's your favorite. Michael.

1851
01:35:12.706 --> 01:35:13.915
Chinese. Some fried chicken.

1852
01:35:13.998 --> 01:35:15.875
Even got these
little red candies you like.

1853
01:35:17.419 --> 01:35:20.964
Thanks. Bill. You can just leave it there.

1854
01:35:21.047 --> 01:35:22.257
I'm not hungry.

1855
01:35:23.133 --> 01:35:24.342
Oh. Okay.

1856
01:35:28.346 --> 01:35:29.764
I'll leave you all to it.

1857
01:35:29.848 --> 01:35:32.475
- Okay. Thank you. Bill.
- Mm-hmm.

1858
01:35:41.025 --> 01:35:44.028
[crowd shouting indistinctly
in the distance]

1859
01:36:00.420 --> 01:36:01.838
I'm sorry. Michael.

1860
01:36:06.176 --> 01:36:07.802
I should have protected you.

1861
01:36:09.637 --> 01:36:13.141
Mother. I don't want
to discuss this right now.

1862
01:36:14.392 --> 01:36:15.477
Okay.

1863
01:36:22.233 --> 01:36:23.735
No one can stop Joseph.

1864
01:36:27.405 --> 01:36:28.490
Nobody.

1865
01:36:37.207 --> 01:36:39.751
You just know that.
no matter what happens.

1866
01:36:40.627 --> 01:36:42.545
I'm gonna be here for you...

1867
01:36:43.546 --> 01:36:45.048
always.

1868
01:36:48.301 --> 01:36:49.719
I should get some rest now. Mother.

1869
01:37:02.941 --> 01:37:05.360
[''I'll Be There (Instrumental)'' playing]

1870
01:37:14.244 --> 01:37:15.870
It's not your fault.

1871
01:37:25.797 --> 01:37:28.967
[exhales]

1872
01:37:34.222 --> 01:37:36.224
[sniffles softly]

1873
01:37:38.560 --> 01:37:40.937
[woman. in distance]
We all need you. Michael!

1874
01:37:42.981 --> 01:37:43.940
[elevator dings]

1875
01:38:16.598 --> 01:38:18.016
[Branca] How are you feeling?

1876
01:38:18.641 --> 01:38:19.934
[Michael] I'm okay.

1877
01:38:20.018 --> 01:38:22.687
You know. I'm still in a lot of pain.

1878
01:38:23.813 --> 01:38:26.107
But the doctors say I'm healing. So...

1879
01:38:26.190 --> 01:38:27.358
Well. that's good news.

1880
01:38:28.276 --> 01:38:29.944
All these kids here...

1881
01:38:31.321 --> 01:38:32.614
They won't fully heal

1882
01:38:32.697 --> 01:38:35.033
and there's burns all over their bodies.

1883
01:38:35.783 --> 01:38:37.201
It just breaks my heart.

1884
01:38:38.161 --> 01:38:39.454
It truly does.

1885
01:38:41.956 --> 01:38:43.625
You know. it got me thinking...

1886
01:38:45.418 --> 01:38:47.086
I need to do more for them.

1887
01:38:48.171 --> 01:38:50.381
How much are we getting for the accident.

1888
01:38:50.465 --> 01:38:52.342
It should be around seven figures.

1889
01:38:52.967 --> 01:38:55.887
I need every penny donated
to the burn center here.

1890
01:38:57.096 --> 01:38:59.182
Please. you got to make that happen.

1891
01:38:59.265 --> 01:39:00.308
Yeah. of course.

1892
01:39:01.559 --> 01:39:03.686
[Michael sighs]

1893
01:39:03.770 --> 01:39:05.480
I'm getting really sleepy.

1894
01:39:07.482 --> 01:39:08.733
These pain meds.

1895
01:39:12.320 --> 01:39:15.365
You get some rest
and I'll come check on you tomorrow.

1896
01:39:16.658 --> 01:39:17.659
Okay.

1897
01:39:17.992 --> 01:39:18.993
[chuckles]

1898
01:39:20.078 --> 01:39:21.537
Did you bring that?

1899
01:39:21.621 --> 01:39:24.248
Oh. the mouse. yeah. That's from me.

1900
01:39:25.416 --> 01:39:26.960
- I love that.
- Good.

1901
01:39:28.211 --> 01:39:29.212
Thank you. Branca.

1902
01:39:29.295 --> 01:39:30.546
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- See you.

1903
01:39:32.507 --> 01:39:34.676
[Joseph] <i>If that boy doesn't go on tour.</i>

1904
01:39:35.593 --> 01:39:37.804
everything we have falls apart.

1905
01:39:37.887 --> 01:39:41.933
I'm talking deals.
sponsorships. our reputation.

1906
01:39:42.016 --> 01:39:43.726
Everything. Everything just gone.

1907
01:39:43.810 --> 01:39:45.144
Everything here.

1908
01:39:46.604 --> 01:39:48.648
The boys won't be able to tour anymore.

1909
01:39:49.273 --> 01:39:50.483
Not without Michael.

1910
01:39:51.109 --> 01:39:53.611
Your son just got out of ICU.

1911
01:39:56.698 --> 01:39:59.367
Michael never wanted to do
The Victory Tour to begin with.

1912
01:39:59.450 --> 01:40:02.078
You planned this entire thing
behind his back.

1913
01:40:06.290 --> 01:40:07.500
[sighs]

1914
01:40:13.881 --> 01:40:16.843
When are you gonna realize
he's on his own path?

1915
01:40:19.721 --> 01:40:22.140
And sometimes. you need
to get out of the way.

1916
01:40:25.768 --> 01:40:27.687
Otherwise. you're gonna lose him.

1917
01:40:30.982 --> 01:40:32.608
What about the other boys?

1918
01:40:33.234 --> 01:40:35.528
They'll find their own path.

1919
01:40:51.586 --> 01:40:53.004
[Michael] <i>You know something. BiII?</i>

1920
01:40:53.588 --> 01:40:56.215
- [Bill] What's that?
- [Michael] God's been very good to me.

1921
01:40:56.299 --> 01:40:58.134
That he has. [chuckles]

1922
01:40:59.302 --> 01:41:00.803
Not just the accident.

1923
01:41:01.512 --> 01:41:03.931
You know. I... I almost died...

1924
01:41:05.558 --> 01:41:07.310
but I was given a second chance.

1925
01:41:08.352 --> 01:41:09.562
Yeah. well...

1926
01:41:10.605 --> 01:41:12.106
God gave you a gift. son.

1927
01:41:13.524 --> 01:41:14.942
A platform...

1928
01:41:16.027 --> 01:41:17.695
to reach the whole world.

1929
01:41:19.572 --> 01:41:20.990
I can't ignore that.

1930
01:41:23.618 --> 01:41:24.535
No.

1931
01:41:27.705 --> 01:41:29.540
I have to shine my light.

1932
01:41:30.458 --> 01:41:32.710
Spread love and joy.

1933
01:41:34.378 --> 01:41:35.588
To heal.

1934
01:41:40.843 --> 01:41:41.761
Yeah.

1935
01:41:44.680 --> 01:41:46.099
That's my destiny.

1936
01:41:48.309 --> 01:41:49.852
I truly believe that.

1937
01:41:50.436 --> 01:41:53.189
Well. why don't we focus
on getting you healthy first?

1938
01:41:53.272 --> 01:41:55.316
Then we can do all those things
you need to do.

1939
01:41:55.399 --> 01:41:56.484
I'm gonna do the tour.

1940
01:41:57.985 --> 01:41:59.070
Are you sure?

1941
01:41:59.904 --> 01:42:01.114
For my family.

1942
01:42:03.574 --> 01:42:04.700
